content.title: Official Singles Chart Top 100 on 22/12/2023
content.description: The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

drupalComments.body:
hey merry xmas mates!  too bad we can't check any replies on disqus esp. for those of us that can't be here each wk...

& that's awesome about mariah!!  back in the 90s on the billboard hot 100 chart, you all should've seen how often she would be in the top 10!  she had hit after hit after hit!  & back in the day, when you had a big hit, it'd be forever 'til it fell out of the top 10.  i have lots of fond memories of mariah dominating the hot 100 top 10 week after week after week.  

& same with george michael...back during this time back in 1987, his 'faith' album was fast becoming a huge success!  & all thoughout 1988 he was hands down 1 of the biggest recording acts here in the states.  he was up there with prince, michael jackson, madonna, whitney, janet, bon jovi, def leppard and the list goes on.  my fave musical year of the 80s!!  everyone had a hit that year over here ;)

drupalComments.title: 9f38d35f-f876-4c4a-a60e-56d10ad9fefc
drupalComments.body:
Like it or loathe it, the Christmas Chart is a fascinating one! In a couple of weeks it's also interesting to see what has bounced back into the Top 100. Great for Wham! The b-side 'Everything She Wants' is a fantastic funky tune which helped the single upon it's initial release in the 1980s and got airplay on it's own merit.
Surprised to see no sign of Sleaford Mods who were contenders with their Shelter charity single 'West End Girls'. It is probably in the vinyl chart this week, I've yet to check.
It's nice to see Paul McCartney's 'Wonderful Christmastime' in the chart. For me it captures the vibes so well.

drupalComments.title: 75d1adc7-01c2-46a0-afe7-eb892b487e6a
drupalComments.body:
I was personally hoping for The Pogues to do it in tribute of Shane and Kirsty, so it’s a real shame that ‘Fairytale Of New York’ isn’t even in the Top 5.

That being said, congratulations to Wham! on finally making it to Christmas Number One for the first time ever! Definitely worthy of the honour given how ‘Last Christmas’ is one of the best-selling songs of all-time in the UK, not just among the festive hits. George Michael would’ve been so pleased about this. RIP to him! 🙏

I’m just glad we finally have a change after five years in a row of LadBaby and their sausage roll parodies.
